<div class="f-w section discussions-latest-section" id="discussions-latest-section">
<div class="m-c">
<div class="gc-6 gc-md-12">
<div class="discussions-latest">
<div class="discussions-latest-header" style="background-image: url('https://s-cdn.phonearena.com/build/wp/images/latest-discussion-header-bg.png')">
<div class="pre-title">
<h2 class="type">Weekly Discussion</h2>
<i class="ic ic-bg-discussion-icon-medium"></i>
<i class="ic ic-bg-discussion-icon-small"></i>
</div>
<div class="title">The Pros and Cons of Removing Chargers from Smartphone Boxes</div>
</div>
<div class="discussions-latest-body">
<div class="content card">
<div class="discussion-author">
<div class="author-picture">
<picture class="square border-primary">
<img src="https://m-cdn.phonearena.com/images/user-avatar/199674-150/Parena1.jpg" alt="MariyanSlavov" loading="lazy">
</picture>
</div>
<div class="author-description">
<div class="author-name">MariyanSlavov</div>
<div class="author-position">Phonearena team</div>
<div class="author-badge">original poster</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="discussion-text">
Welcome to another controversial topic: smartphone retail boxes. Do we need a charging brick inside? What about a cable? We all know that Apple started it back in 2020 when the company removed the charger from the retail box of the iPhone 12 family, but almost everyone has since followed suit. Some companies (looking at you, Sony!) have also removed the cable and now sell just a paper box with a phone inside. Do you believe all the eco-reasons, or do you think it&apos;s just snake oil, smoke, and mirrors?
</div>
</div>
<div class="button-container">
<a class="join home-jd" href="https://www.phonearena.com/discussions/The-Pros-and-Cons-of-Removing-Chargers-from-Smartphone-Boxes_id151482">Join Discussion</a>
<a class="browse home-all-d" href="https://www.phonearena.com/discussions">Browse All Discussions<i class="ic ic-arrow-right"></i></a>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
